post_survey.music_making: Not a musician and very bad at all forms of music
post_survey.activities: work, chores, playing videogames, crafting, art
post_survey.habit_change: As a kid I mostly listened to CDs and listened to music I learned from my parents before branching out into popular artists to teens at the time and musicians I heard from movies/shows. Lots of angsty emo stuff as a teen. Got into more experimental stuff in high school, like Tom Waits. Started branching out. Used an iPod + iTunes for the most part up until I was out of college (2017).
post_survey.habits: Nowadays, I'm finally mainly using Spotify, though I still have an old iPod classic that I use. I tend to find new artists via Spotify's discover playlists and songs featured in shows I like.
